definitions.text: shake, quiver, or throb; move back and forth rapidly, usually in an uncontrolled manner
move or swing from side to side regularly
examples: the needle on the meter was oscillating

definitions.text: be undecided about something; waver between conflicting positions or courses of action
examples: He oscillates between accepting the new position and retirement
The sound resonates well in this theater

definitions.text: feel sudden intense sensation or emotion
examples: he was thrilled by the speed and the roar of the engine
